{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d56a5a31-081e-41ae-ae40-7f9f0d52bc83","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()` called directly\n\n```python\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\nThis is hard to test because you can't easily control or mock the time in unit tests.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `django.utils.timezone.now()` and inject it or use `freezegun`/`time-machine` for testing:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis gives you timezone-awareness **and** is easily mockable with `@freeze_time` or `unittest.mock.patch('django.utils.timezone.now')`.\n\nThe project is small — only one file with one offending call. Want me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"88a583c9-2d79-4b24-b7c7-2172ef994fa3","outputTokens":206,"requestId":"BC24:2ED298:6D259E:7E853B:69FAA91C"},"id":"d02a4cb9-db67-434a-a2dc-59df7a5781a4","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:36:17.983Z","parentId":"1f9d8204-00e9-4b50-a670-1a7e297df4d1"}
